# Translation runner audit logs land here as <ISO-timestamp>.jsonl, one row per
# processed translation. Each line records: row_id, locale, source_key, status,
# cost_usd, and (on flag) flagged_by or error.
#
# Files in this directory are committed for audit purposes — they're small,
# append-only, and useful for cost tracking + post-mortem of flagged batches.
